Interface IClientTerminologyBrowser<C,K>

  • Type Parameters:
    C - the concept type
    K - the concept unique identifier type
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IClientTerminologyAndRefSetBrowser<R,C,K>, IFilterClientTerminologyBrowser<C,K>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ClientTerminologyBrowserAdapter, EmptyTerminologyBrowser, FilteredRefSetMemberBrowser2, FilteredTerminologyBrowser

    public interface IClientTerminologyBrowser<C,K>
    Interface for browsing a hierarchy of concepts on the client side.

      • exist

        Map<String,Boolean> exist(Collection<String> componentIds)
        Checks whether the components identified by their terminology specific unique IDs exist on the given branch. Returns with a map, where the keys are the component IDs and the values are true or false whether the component exists or not.
        Parameters:
        componentIds - the terminology specific unique IDs.
        Returns:
        map where each ID is mapped to true or false whether it exists or not.
